title: The passage of our most drad Soueraigne Lady Quene Elyzabeth through the citie of London to westminster the daye before her coronacion Anno 1558. Cum priuilegio.
publisher: In fletestrete within Temple barre, at the signe of the hand and starre, by Richard Tottill,
notes: The passage was made in January 1559 (civil calendar).
First published in 1559 as: The quenes majesties passage through the citie of London to westminster the daye before her coronacion.
C inner forme is reimposed from STC 7589.5.
Running title reads: The receiuing of the Queenes maiestie.
Reproduction of the original in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery.
